"uri":"a::place::352d9080-eddc-11ed-b151-a5b31dedf00a","name":"Marina di Stabia","coordinates":{"latitude":40.72334082612881,"longitude":14.47082520092881},"country":"Italy"},"cruisingCapacity":12,"builtYear":2007,"refitYear":2024,"cruiseSpeed":25,"cabinLayout":[{"label":"Master Cabin","value":"1"},{"label":"VIP Cabin","value":"1"},{"label":"Twin Convertible Cabin","value":"1"}],"cabins":3,"bathrooms":3,"length":18.2,"beam":5.59,"draft":1.08,"engines":"2 x Caterpillar 1000 HP","amenities":[{"label":"Sundeck"}],"entertainment":["Wi-Fi","TV Sat in all the cabins","BOSE Audio Wireless/Bluetooth system"]},"crew":[{"name":"Fabio Nitti","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819281976::vessel::986fb160-34bf-11f0-bfb5-e754accc3a56::assets::f4bb8120-454e-11f0-80eb-ef19d19e849d/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Fabio was born in Puglia, Italy, in 1996 and learned to sail from an early age in the waters of the South Adriatic Sea. He graduated from the Naval School of Bari in 2017. Shortly after, he decided to embark as a deckhand on a tanker ship, where he spent over three years significantly developing his nautical skills and knowledge, also earning his Officer qualification.\n\nHe entered the yachting industry in 2020, working as First Officer on two motor yachts over 90 feet and as Captain on smaller charter yachts along the Amalfi Coast. Fabio joined Magistra at the beginning of this year, personally overseeing the refit process through to the launch in April.  He is competent, highly skilled, and reliable in all situations, even the most challenging ones. His ever-present smile and positive attitude are qualities that truly set him apart.\n"},{"name":"Martina D'ANIELLO","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819281976::vessel::986fb160-34bf-11f0-bfb5-e754accc3a56::assets::0c49c720-454f-11f0-80eb-ef19d19e849d/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Martina was born in Castellamare just where Magistra is berthed and makes charters. \nShe is nice and polite Stewardess who lov